cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.LG

This paper deals with the task of editing digital bilingual dictionaries, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques (cs.CL and cs.IR). The use of a programming language to manipulate the structure and text of the lexicographic data suggests a focus on data management and database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the advantages of the proposed paradigm, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
